PDA_S_0_61   = "Let me explain you VECTOR!!!";
PDA_D_0_61   = "22/09/2255";
PDA_PI_0_61  = "PORTRA10";
PDA_E_0_61   = "\c[PDASUB1]To:\c- Dawn Collins\n\c[PDASUB1]From:\c- Sal\n\c[PDASUB1]Subject:\c- Let me explain you VECTOR!!!\n\nIt's been one month we are fighting these fucking aliens!\nWhile you were "playing around" with our little alien friends, I managed to create something that could be useful to you and our comrades... but specially to you! I called it V.E.C.T.O.R... Virtual Encounter Combat and Tactical Operations Recursion.\nWhat? It's not a stupid dumb name, I asked our AOS AI assistant to give me some name ideas and... yup, it's quite dumb.\n\nBy the way I see you are already inside! The chest in front of you is used to modify and upgrade your weapons using weapons parts or buy ammo with money. The weapons parts can be used to enable an upgrade or you can get the weapon parts back by disabling that upgrade, so you can constantly decide what weapon to power up based on your ammo or situation.\n\nWhen you cross the red circle around the chest, the game wil start! You will encounter random enemies each wave, and of course the number and power of your enemies will increase as you progress in the game, wave after wave. At the end of each wave, you can select a prize that can help you: it can be a weapon, a temporary ability, a powerup, or just some health, armor, money or weapon parts. You just need to be lucky, maybe a Railgun will appear!! Unfortunately you can use it only for one wave eheheh!\n\nHave fun and please! Do not crash VECTOR by gibbing too many enemies!";